## IMAGE GENERATION PROMPT WRITING RULES (CRITICAL)

When writing the **Image Generation Prompt**, you are creating instructions for an AI image generator. Follow these rules:

### ❌ **NEVER INCLUDE IN THE PROMPT:**
- Degree symbols (°) - Write "tilted 5 degrees right" NOT "tilted 5° right"
- Percentage symbols (%) - Write "50 percent" NOT "50%"
- Technical notation like "pt" when describing sizes - Write "360 point" NOT "360pt"
- Measurement abbreviations like "px" - Write "pixel" NOT "px"
- Math symbols - Write out fully ("4.5 to 1 ratio" NOT "4.5:1")
- Instruction markers like "CRITICAL:", "NOTE:", "IMPORTANT:" - These are meta-instructions, not design elements
- Reference to rules or guidelines - Only describe what to create, not how you're following rules

### ✅ **CORRECT PROMPT WRITING:**
```
Size: 360 point (MASSIVE)
Position: CENTER HORIZONTAL
Tilted 5 degrees right
Text occupies 50 percent vertical height
Contrast ratio 4.5 to 1 for readability
```

### ❌ **INCORRECT PROMPT WRITING:**
```
Size: 360pt (MASSIVE)
Position: CENTER HORIZONTAL
Tilted 5° right
Text occupies 50% vertical height
Contrast ratio 4.5:1 for readability
NOTE: Make sure text is readable
CRITICAL: Follow contrast rules
```

**WHY:** The image generator may interpret symbols and technical notation as text to be rendered on the image itself, causing visual errors. Write naturally and descriptively.

